<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-06-21T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-06-21T18:00:00-05:00" n="14" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d14">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">710.1012 Anti-War/93 supp.:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Denmark</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Owen</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-06-21T19:00:00-04:00">June 21, 1934—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>19. Department’s 15, June 9, 1934, 3 p.m. The Argentine Anti-War Pact has
                            just been ratified by this Government, and you may express to the Danish
                            Government our sincere belief in the efficacy of the Pact and of our
                            hope that the other nations of the world will become signatories to
                            it.</p>
                        <p>Similar instructions are being sent to the Legations at Stockholm and
                            Oslo.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>